<br>
Against a competant well equiped opponent, you're in real trouble, since all your attacks are magical, and they can pump up their magic resist to the point where you can't cast anything.  Until that point, however, root is your best friend.  Self healing is fun too.<br>
<br>
Also, dispell dispell dispell.  Don't want your opponent buffed!<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalninil@firionavie>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 801<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 11:57:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics in duel</span><hr size=1> well ...<br>
<br>
we aren't the best duelest out there ..<br>
<br>
at your level alot of folks have't got a set of resist gear so you could possiblely melee , dd them. or root them.<br>
<br>
as things progress folks will start to pick up mr gear and render our offenceive spells useless. then its mostly jousting and self healing.<br>
<br>
movement is key to dueling have sow potions and j boots you win if they don't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=priestessnaeneori>Priestess Naeneori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Priestess of Pain,<br>dancin naked</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 12:12:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics in duel</span><hr size=1> clerics shouldnt duel monks, SK's or warriors....with cunning and thought, you can beat anyone else....(I didnt say it was easy, BTW....just that its possible)  I did beat a SK in a duel once with a cleric but I think he let me win *evil grin* <p><img src="http://noirdaila.homestead.com/files/newnae.JPG"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corrinofv>CorrinoFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/9/02 11:30:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics in duel</span><hr size=1>  The key for me, has always been in my melee skills. Never stand still, have SoW potions<br>
 Debuff them at the begining of the match. <br>
 Save plenty of your mana for personal heals. <br>
 Bashing is the sh** Against other casters. <br>
 Darkness is always a favorite too, if they dont have thier spells hotkeyed, they are skrewed-so keep your divination up to par for dueling.<br>
 When fighting anything other than SK's fear their pets. Sk pets are too weak to worry about.<br>
 Your Divine aura will be a heavy weapon too. Use it when you think they are going to use their strongest offensives against you. The trick is to keep them distracted, or bluff them into using their strongest attack. Skill at bluffing them will come as you duel more and more.<br>
 Dont get discouraged! <br>
 Run and med if you need to! There is no shame in this, infact i encourage it. Lull them to sleep with your slow arse offensives, and you win. Simple ehh?<br>
 Good luck<br>
<br>
Corrino D'Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=anezkiadevine>Anezkia Devine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 7:48:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics in duel</span><hr size=1> Clerics are great duelers!  I have only battled a few lately, because most have refused hehe.  But chalk up a win for me against a bard, wizard, and mage (all the same level or one or two higher than me)<br>
<br>
My old guild used to hold many pvp events in the arena so it was good practice I guess <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway....root, blind, and stun are the best weapons I have found.  I can't give away all my secrets...but someone who cannot see is not very dangerous hehe...and root is nice for keeping out of melee range. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karivian>karivian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/02 2:44:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics in duel</span><hr size=1> Dispell, fear pets, bash, Yaulp, Mark of Retribution, Mark of the Righteous (for melees), root, blind, stun, heal, potions and of course, dont for get to run when ya gotta!<br>
<br>
Of course we are not a dueling class really.  My best defense is /decline and then hire and buff someone else to duel for me!  j/k<br>
